id: pm-alnj
title: "GH-474: pm search --limit support in hybrid mode"
description: "Dogfood GH-474: hybrid search can return many results and --limit (available in keyword mode) is not honored/available in hybrid mode, breaking agent token budgets. Duplicate check: searched hybrid search limit — pm-6mn1 (closed, M4) covered limit=0 determinism only; this is general --limit support in hybrid mode."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-experience,"area:search",gh-issue,token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-07-06T21:09:28.492Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-07T08:34:55.312Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: pm search --mode hybrid honors --limit identically to keyword mode (applied after fusion ranking); documented in help/contracts; spec covers limit interaction with hybrid result fusion including limit=0 determinism from pm-6mn1
parent: pm-ydp6
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: Implemented hybrid search limit parity by keeping semantic candidates at least max_results wide through fusion and applying the requested --limit only after final ranking/truncation.
expected_result: pm search --mode hybrid honors --limit like keyword search while preserving pm-6mn1 limit=0 deterministic empty-result behavior.
actual_result: "Packed-install dogfood confirmed npx pm search alpha --json --limit 1 returns filters.limit=1 and one hit; zero-limit regression remains covered; focused/full tests, coverage, Greptile, and PR checks passed."
